{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nAn OPTIONAL, isolated backfill adapter that mines this machine's Claude Code session transcripts to reconstruct the LOCAL env/integration-diagnosis history (and corroborate attempts/replanning/recovery), which no structural signal captures. Output is LLM-classified and clearly labeled low-confidence; the core command does not depend on this adapter.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/adapters/__init__.py`, `src/rebar/metrics/adapters/claude_transcripts.py` ‚Äî new isolated adapter (imported only by the backfill script, never by the core command).\n- `scripts/backfill_transcripts.py` ‚Äî new: targeted extraction (grep error signatures) -> classify -> write labeled snapshots.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_transcript_adapter.py` ‚Äî new.\n\n## Approach\nBecause all development happened on one machine, the transcripts are a near-complete local record of env toil that leaves no structural trace. To keep the harness portable, the adapter is optional and quarantined behind the backfill script ‚Äî a parallel adapter could target another harness. It is a targeted pass: an **error-signature grep** over the transcript JSONL (patterns such as `LLMUnavailableError`, `ConnectionError`/`connection refused`, `ModuleNotFoundError`, `command not found`, `No such file`, HTTP `429`, `timed out`) selects candidate lines, then a **deterministic keyword/regex classifier** (NOT an LLM ‚Äî so the adapter and its test are self-contained and reproducible, with no model call or human-calibration gate) maps each signature to the classification enum. Every emitted value carries `source=backfill_classified, confidence=classified` ‚Äî that label IS the honest low-confidence signal, and it segregates these values from authoritative structural series. The classification enum (`env_setup`, `dependency`, `integration`, `tooling`, `none`) and the JSON output schema are defined in the adapter module.\n\n**Normative pattern‚Üíenum routing table** (first match wins; case-insensitive substring/regex over the transcript line):\n- `env_setup` ‚Üê `ModuleNotFoundError`, `ImportError`, `No such file or directory`, `virtualenv`/`venv` activation errors, `command not found`.\n- `dependency` ‚Üê `pip`/`uv` resolution errors, `version conflict`, `Could not find a version`, `incompatible`.\n- `integration` ‚Üê `ConnectionError`, `connection refused`, `timed out`/`ReadTimeout`, HTTP `429`/`5xx`, `LLMUnavailableError`.\n- `tooling` ‚Üê `git` errors, `ruff`/`mypy`/`pytest` invocation failures, `Permission denied`.\n- `none` ‚Üê a candidate line matching no rule above (dropped, not emitted).\n\n**Emitted record JSON schema** (one per classified interval): `{\"kind\": <one of the enum values>, \"signature\": <the matched pattern/string>, \"ts\": <ISO-8601 of the transcript entry>, \"source\": \"backfill_classified\", \"confidence\": \"classified\"}`. The AC assertions (`jq -e`) target `.kind` and `.source`/`.confidence`.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (fixture JSONL transcripts): a transcript with a known env-failure signature is extracted and classified into an `env_setup` interval; a clean transcript yields none; output carries the classified label.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_transcript_adapter.py` passes: a fixture JSONL transcript containing a known env-failure signature (e.g. a `ModuleNotFoundError` line) is extracted and deterministically classified into at least one interval tagged `source=backfill_classified`, `confidence=classified` (`jq -e`); a clean transcript yields 0. No LLM/network call occurs (the classifier is deterministic).\n- [ ] the portability guard holds: a unit test asserts the CORE metrics package does NOT import the adapter ‚Äî specifically that `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py` and `src/rebar/metrics/__init__.py` (the modules that exist today) do not import `adapters.claude_transcripts` (assert by scanning each module's source for the adapter import). The `rebar metrics` command's own isolation from adapters is enforced by ticket 9a5a's portability-guard AC ‚Äî this ticket does NOT assert against `_commands/metrics.py` (which 9a5a delivers), to avoid a vacuously-passing scan of a not-yet-existing file.\n- [ ] `scripts/backfill_transcripts.py` is exercised: a test invokes its entry point over a fixture transcript dir and asserts it emits the labeled classified records (so the script ‚Äî not just the adapter ‚Äî is covered).\n- [ ] the classification enum (`env_setup`, `dependency`, `integration`, `tooling`, `none`) and output schema are defined in the adapter module ‚Äî test asserts the enum has exactly these values."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784454166204913001,"uuid":"f685fddf-3f68-44b2-ad67-408d007cb367"}